# Brand & Styling

## Source of truth

`src/styles/tokens.css` defines brand CSS variables. Tailwind v4 theme tokens live in `@theme` inside `global.css`.

| Token | Value | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `--ab-green` / `ab-green` | `#006A52` | Primary — CTAs, headlines |
| `--ab-gold` / `ab-gold` | `#D6A02A` | Accents, numerals |
| `--ab-beige` / `ab-beige` | `#D3BC8D` | Use minimally (badges, highlights) |
| `--ab-neon` / `ab-neon` | `#00FF1F` | **Digital only** — focus, live indicators |

## Hard rules

- Never recreate the AB monogram or `1889` numeral from type — use `src/assets/brand/` SVGs
- Neon green is on-screen only; never for print assets
- Sponsor lockup: AB primary, vertical rule, side-by-side; owl crest ≠ monogram in lockups
- Headlines: uppercase, heavy weight (`font-black`), tight letter-spacing
- Body copy: mixed case, never justified

## Styling approach

- Tailwind utilities for layout/spacing — see `tailwind.mdc` for class patterns
- Inline `style=` for one-off brand values (clamp typography, gradients) — match existing pages
- Prefer token/Tailwind colours over raw hex when adding new styles
- Fonts: ABC Camera Plain (self-hosted in `public/fonts/`, licensed); Helvetica fallback

## Layout patterns

- Max content width: `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16`
- Hero heights: `clamp(...)` via inline style
- Dark sections: `#0A0A09` / `rich-black`
